   "taught_in": "Part 1, p.52 (with Lesson 5)",
   "explain_en": "A bare consonant cannot form a word. Give it a vowel and you get a GUNITAKSHARA. ದ್ + ಏ = ದೇ, ವ್ + ಅ = ವ, ರ್ + ಉ = ರು, which together make the real word ದೇವರು. Every consonant takes 16 vowels, so it has 16 gunitaksharas. When two or more CONSONANTS join instead (ಅಪ್ಪ, ಅಮ್ಮ, ಅಸ್ತ್ರ) that is a SAMYUKTAKSHARA.",
